# GOV.UK Frontend theming via app overrides

Theme and brand GOV.UK Frontend **only** through this app’s styles — do not fork or patch vendor GOV.UK Frontend CSS/Sass.

- Use the packaged GOV.UK Frontend styles as shipped (imported from `govuk-frontend`, e.g. in `src/frontend/scss/main.scss`)
- Do **not** edit files under `node_modules/govuk-frontend` or vendor-copied GOV.UK stylesheets
- Put theme/brand customisation in **app SCSS/CSS** under `src/frontend/scss/` (and related app stylesheets): Sass settings/layers before or after the official import, or app override classes — not patched Design System source
- Prefer official GOV.UK Frontend Sass/CSS API (settings, tools, overrides supported by the package) over rewriting component CSS by hand
- Do not duplicate large chunks of GOV.UK component CSS in the app; extend or override narrowly
- If GOV.UK Frontend CSS must change for a bug/upgrade, bump the `govuk-frontend` package — do not maintain a vendored CSS fork
- Keep theming changes consistent with accessible UI priorities and `.cursor/rules/prefer-govuk-over-axe.mdc`
